juniAtmMIB.name: juniAtmMIB

revisions.description: Removed support for: juniAtmIfSvcSignallingTable juniAtmIfPnniRccTable juniAtmSubIfAddress juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigTable.

Added the following to juniAtmCircuitOamTable: juniAtmCircuitInOamF5EndToEndLoopbackCmds juniAtmCircuitInOamF5EndToEndLoopbackRsps juniAtmCircuitInOamF5SegmentLoopbackCmds juniAtmCircuitInOamF5SegmentLoopbackRsps juniAtmCircuitOutOamF5EndToEndLoopbackCmds juniAtmCircuitOutOamF5EndToEndLoopbackRsps juniAtmCircuitOutOamF5SegmentLoopbackCmds juniAtmCircuitOutOamF5SegmentLoopbackRsps juniAtmCircuitOamUpCount juniAtmCircuitOamDownCount juniAtmCircuitOamRetryFrequency juniAtmCircuitOamAlarmDownCount juniAtmCircuitOamAlarmClearTimeout Added the following to juniAtmF4FlowOamEndToEndStatsTable: juniAtmF4FlowEndToEndInLoopbackCmds juniAtmF4FlowEndToEndInLoopbackRsps juniAtmF4FlowEndToEndOutLoopbackCmds juniAtmF4FlowEndToEndOutLoopbackRsps Added the following to juniAtmF4FlowOamSegmentStatsTable: juniAtmF4FlowSegmentInLoopbackCmds juniAtmF4FlowSegmentInLoopbackRsps juniAtmF4FlowSegmentOutLoopbackCmds juniAtmF4FlowSegmentOutLoopbackRsps
Added aal0 and aal5 values to juniAtmSubIfVccType enumeration. Added ATM Martini cell aggregation configuration objects. Added profile override support. Added bulk-configuration modification support.

Added second generation E-series platform support: Imported JuniInterfaceLocationType and JuniInterfaceLocationValue from Juniper-TC to replace JuniAtmLocationType and JuniAtmLocationValue textual conventions, respectively.
Added support to export the subinterface description to the line cards. Added advisory receive support for subinterfaces.
Added JuniAtmLocationType and JuniAtmLocationValue textual conventions. Added juniAtmSubIfLocationType and juniAtmSubIfLocationTable.
Added F4 flow OAM circuit support. Added ATM VP description support. Added bulk circuit configuration support. Corrected enumeration values for UNI signalling versions.
Replaced Unisphere names with Juniper names. Changed the juniAtmVcPingProbeCount Range to match CLI. Added null value for juniAtmSubIfVccType.
Added receive bandwith support to CAC. Added E164 public addressing support. Added PNNI RCC table support. Added ATM1483 interface MTU config support.
Added support for CAC used bandwidth. Added ATM switched virtual connection (SVC) support. Added juniAtmSubIfAddress to the juniAtmSubIfTable.
Added support for connection admission control (CAC).
Added support from ATM traffic shaping.

Added support for NBMA map lists. Added support for ATM ping. Changed juniAtmSubIfVccVcd and juniAtmIfIlmiVcd ranges to (0..2147483647). Added range to juniAtmIfCapabilityMaxVcd. Added rtVbr service catagory to juniAtmSubIfVccTable. Added support for OAM cell filter. Added PVC counter for reveived unknown protocol.
Added autoconfig value for juniAtmSubIfVccType. Added in/out summary cell counters. Added juniVpTunnelServiceCategory to juniAtmVpTunnelTable. Added support for atm interface capability traversal.
Initial version of this MIB module.

JuniAtmNbmaMapName.name: JuniAtmNbmaMapName
JuniAtmNbmaMapName.description: An administratively assigned map name. Represents textual information taken from the NVT ASCII character set. The name must be unique per system.
JuniAtmNbmaMapName.reference: RFC 854: NVT ASCII character set. See SNMPv2-TC.DisplayString DESCRIPTION for a summary.

JuniAtmNbmaMapNameOrNull.name: JuniAtmNbmaMapNameOrNull
JuniAtmNbmaMapNameOrNull.description: An administratively assigned map name. Represents textual information taken from the NVT ASCII character set. The name must be unique per system. Differs from JuniAtmNbmaMapName in that it permits a zero-length string.
JuniAtmNbmaMapNameOrNull.reference: RFC 854: NVT ASCII character set. See SNMPv2-TC.DisplayString DESCRIPTION for a summary.

JuniAtmLocationType.name: JuniAtmLocationType
JuniAtmLocationType.description: Obsolete description of the platform-dependent interpretation of a JuniAtmLocationValue object. This textual convention has been relpaced by Juniper-TC.JuniInterfaceLocationType.

JuniAtmLocationValue.name: JuniAtmLocationValue
JuniAtmLocationValue.description: Obsolete value of a platform-dependent interface location, represented as an OCTET STRING. A corresponding JuniAtmLocationType object identified the mapping of octets to location elements, e.g. 'slot.port'. This textual convention has been replaced by Juniper-TC.JuniInterfaceLocationValue.

juniAtmNextIfIndex.name: juniAtmNextIfIndex
juniAtmNextIfIndex.description: Coordinate ifIndex value allocation for entries in juniAtmIfTable. A GET of this object returns the next available ifIndex value to be used to create an entry in the associated interface table; or zero, if no valid ifIndex value is available. This object also returns a value of zero when it is the lexicographic successor of a varbind presented in an SNMP GETNEXT or GETBULK request, for which circumstance it is assumed that ifIndex allocation is unintended. Successive GETs will typically return different values, thus avoiding collisions among cooperating management clients seeking to create table entries simultaneously.

juniAtmIfTable.name: juniAtmIfTable
juniAtmIfTable.description: This table contains entries for ATM interfaces present in the system.

juniAtmIfEntry.name: juniAtmIfEntry
juniAtmIfEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of an ATM interface. Creating/deleting entries in this table causes corresponding entries for be created/deleted in ifTable/ifXTable/juniIfTable.

juniAtmIfIndex.name: juniAtmIfIndex
juniAtmIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the ATM interface. When creating entries in this table, suitable values for this object are determined by reading juniAtmNextIfIndex.

juniAtmIfRowStatus.name: juniAtmIfRowStatus
juniAtmIfRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy To create an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: juniAtmIfRowStatus juniAtmIfLowerIfIndex In addition, when creating an entry the following condition must hold: A value for juniAtmIfIndex must have been determined previously, by reading juniAtmNextIfIndex. A corresponding entry in ifTable/ifXTable/juniIfTable is created or destroyed as a result of creating/destroying an entry in this table.

juniAtmIfLowerIfIndex.name: juniAtmIfLowerIfIndex
juniAtmIfLowerIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of an interface over which this ATM interface is to be layered. A value of zero indicates no layering. An implementation may choose to require that a nonzero value be configured at entry creation.

juniAtmIfIlmiVpi.name: juniAtmIfIlmiVpi
juniAtmIfIlmiVpi.description: The VPI of the ILMI of a major ATM interface.

juniAtmIfIlmiVci.name: juniAtmIfIlmiVci
juniAtmIfIlmiVci.description: The VCI of the ILMI of a major ATM interface.

juniAtmIfIlmiVcd.name: juniAtmIfIlmiVcd
juniAtmIfIlmiVcd.description: An integer identifier for the ILMI, used in conjunction with the command-line interface. The value must be unique among VCs configured on the same ATM interface.

juniAtmIfIlmiPollFrequency.name: juniAtmIfIlmiPollFrequency
juniAtmIfIlmiPollFrequency.description: The amount of time in seconds between successive transmissions of ILMI messages on this interface for the purpose of detecting loss of ILMI connectivity. The distinguished value zero disables ILMI connectivity procedures on this interface.

juniAtmIfIlmiAdminState.name: juniAtmIfIlmiAdminState
juniAtmIfIlmiAdminState.description: The administrative status of ILMI in the ATM interface.

juniAtmIfUniVersion.name: juniAtmIfUniVersion
juniAtmIfUniVersion.description: Use to specify the User Network Interface (UNI) the router should use when ILMI link auto determination is unsuccesful or ILMI is disabled.

juniAtmIfOamCellRxAdminState.name: juniAtmIfOamCellRxAdminState
juniAtmIfOamCellRxAdminState.description: Use to specify the OAM Cell Receive Administrative state on this interface.

juniAtmIfInCells.name: juniAtmIfInCells
juniAtmIfInCells.description: The total number of cells received on this major interface.

juniAtmIfOutCells.name: juniAtmIfOutCells
juniAtmIfOutCells.description: The total number of cells transmitted on this major interface.

juniAtmIfVcCount.name: juniAtmIfVcCount
juniAtmIfVcCount.description: The total number of circuits configured on this interface.

juniAtmIfMapGroup.name: juniAtmIfMapGroup
juniAtmIfMapGroup.description: The NBMA map group this interface is associated with.

juniAtmIfCacAdminState.name: juniAtmIfCacAdminState
juniAtmIfCacAdminState.description: The administrative staus of CAC on this ATM major interface.

juniAtmIfCacUbrWeight.name: juniAtmIfCacUbrWeight
juniAtmIfCacUbrWeight.description: The bandwidth associated with every UBR and UBR with PCR connection configured on the ATM major interface. This value is used for CAC computation. The units are kilo-bits per second (kbps).

juniAtmIfCacSubscriptionBandwidth.name: juniAtmIfCacSubscriptionBandwidth
juniAtmIfCacSubscriptionBandwidth.description: The subscribed bandwidth of the ATM major interface. If this value is not specified or set to 0, the effective port bandwidth is used. When a Get operation is performed the current effective bandwidth is returned. The units are kilo-bits per second (kbps).

juniAtmIfCacAvailableBandwidth.name: juniAtmIfCacAvailableBandwidth
juniAtmIfCacAvailableBandwidth.description: The available bandwidth in Tx direction of the ATM major interface. As connections are added or deleted on the interface, this value is updated. The units are kilo-bits per second (kbps).

juniAtmIfCacAvailableBandwidthRx.name: juniAtmIfCacAvailableBandwidthRx
juniAtmIfCacAvailableBandwidthRx.description: The available bandwidth in Rx direction of the ATM major interface. As connections are added or deleted on the interface, this value is updated. The units are kilo-bits per second (kbps).

juniAtmIfE164Autoconversion.name: juniAtmIfE164Autoconversion
juniAtmIfE164Autoconversion.description: The status of E164 autoconversion feature in the ATM interface.

juniAtmIfE164Gateway.name: juniAtmIfE164Gateway
juniAtmIfE164Gateway.description: The status of E164 gateway feature in the ATM interface.

juniAtmIfE164OneToOneAddrTrans.name: juniAtmIfE164OneToOneAddrTrans
juniAtmIfE164OneToOneAddrTrans.description: The status of E164 one-to-one address translation feature in the ATM interface.

juniAtmIfOamCellFilter.name: juniAtmIfOamCellFilter
juniAtmIfOamCellFilter.description: The type of OAM cells to discard when juniAtmIfOamCellRxAdminState is set to oamCellAdminStateDisabled. The value oamCellFilterAlarm discards received OAM AIS and RDI cells. The value oamCellFilterAll discards all received OAM cells. Note that when juniAtmIfOamCellRxAdminState is set to oamCellAdminStateEnabled, this object has no effect.

juniAtmIfCacUsedBandwidthUpper.name: juniAtmIfCacUsedBandwidthUpper
juniAtmIfCacUsedBandwidthUpper.description: The most significant 32 bits of the CAC used bandwidth on the ATM major interface. The least significant 32 bits of the CAC used bandwidth are specified by juniAtmIfCacUsedBandwidthLower.

juniAtmIfCacUsedBandwidthLower.name: juniAtmIfCacUsedBandwidthLower
juniAtmIfCacUsedBandwidthLower.description: The least significant 32 bits of the CAC used bandwidth on the ATM major interface. The most significant 32 bits of the CAC used bandwidth are specified by juniAtmIfCacUsedBandwidthUpper.

juniAtmIfAssociatedVcClassId.name: juniAtmIfAssociatedVcClassId
juniAtmIfAssociatedVcClassId.description: The integer identifier of the ATM VC class associated with this ATM interface. A value for this identifier is determined by locating or creating an ATM VC class name in the juniAtmVcClassNameTable. A value of 0 means no VC class association exists for this interface.

juniAtmPvcStatisticsTable.name: juniAtmPvcStatisticsTable
juniAtmPvcStatisticsTable.description: This table contains statistics for PVC entries.

juniAtmPvcStatisticsEntry.name: juniAtmPvcStatisticsEntry
juniAtmPvcStatisticsEntry.description: Each entry provides statistics on an ATM PVC.

juniAtmPvcStatsIfIndex.name: juniAtmPvcStatsIfIndex
juniAtmPvcStatsIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the ATM interface.

juniAtmPvcStatsVpi.name: juniAtmPvcStatsVpi
juniAtmPvcStatsVpi.description: The VPI of the ATM VCC used by this ATM interface and PVC.

juniAtmPvcStatsVci.name: juniAtmPvcStatsVci
juniAtmPvcStatsVci.description: The VCI of the ATM VCC used by this ATM interface and PVC.

juniAtmPvcStatsInCellErrors.name: juniAtmPvcStatsInCellErrors
juniAtmPvcStatsInCellErrors.description: Received cells dropped due to errors.

juniAtmPvcStatsinPacketErrors.name: juniAtmPvcStatsinPacketErrors
juniAtmPvcStatsinPacketErrors.description: Received packets dropped due to errors.

juniAtmPvcStatsOutCellErrors.name: juniAtmPvcStatsOutCellErrors
juniAtmPvcStatsOutCellErrors.description: Cells not transmitted due to errors.

juniAtmPvcStatsOutPacketErrors.name: juniAtmPvcStatsOutPacketErrors
juniAtmPvcStatsOutPacketErrors.description: Packets not transmitted due to errors.

juniAtmPvcStatsInPacketUnknownProtocol.name: juniAtmPvcStatsInPacketUnknownProtocol
juniAtmPvcStatsInPacketUnknownProtocol.description: Received packets that are discarded because the interface can not discern or is not configured to support this protocol.

juniAtmVpTunnelTable.name: juniAtmVpTunnelTable
juniAtmVpTunnelTable.description: This table contains entries for ATM VP Tunnels present in the system.

juniAtmVpTunnelEntry.name: juniAtmVpTunnelEntry
juniAtmVpTunnelEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of an ATM VP Tunnel.

juniAtmVpTunnelIfIndex.name: juniAtmVpTunnelIfIndex
juniAtmVpTunnelIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the ATM interface. The value of this object is the same as the juniAtmIfIndex object in the juniAtmIfTable. Entries in this table cannot be created unless the underlying ATM interface entry is created first in the juniAtmIfTable.

juniAtmVpTunnelVpi.name: juniAtmVpTunnelVpi
juniAtmVpTunnelVpi.description: The VPI value for this VP tunnel entry.

juniAtmVpTunnelKbps.name: juniAtmVpTunnelKbps
juniAtmVpTunnelKbps.description: The tunnel rate in kilobits per second (kbps) for this entry.

juniAtmVpTunnelRowStatus.name: juniAtmVpTunnelRowStatus
juniAtmVpTunnelRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy To create an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: juniAtmVpTunnelRowStatus juniAtmVpTunnelKbps In addition, when creating an entry the following condition must hold: A correponding juniAtmVpTunnelIfIndex value must have been created in the juniAtmIfTable previously.

juniAtmVpTunnelServiceCategory.name: juniAtmVpTunnelServiceCategory
juniAtmVpTunnelServiceCategory.description: The ATM service category for the tunnel.

juniAtmIfCapabilityTable.name: juniAtmIfCapabilityTable
juniAtmIfCapabilityTable.description: This table contains entries for ATM interfaces present in the system.

juniAtmIfCapabilityEntry.name: juniAtmIfCapabilityEntry
juniAtmIfCapabilityEntry.description: Each entry describes the capabilities of an ATM interface. A management client can use this table to determine differences in the configurable level of support across entries in this table.

juniAtmIfCapabilityIndex.name: juniAtmIfCapabilityIndex
juniAtmIfCapabilityIndex.description: The ifIndex of the ATM interface. The value of this object is the same as juniAtmIfIndex in the juniAtmIfTable.

juniAtmIfCapabilityTrafficShaping.name: juniAtmIfCapabilityTrafficShaping
juniAtmIfCapabilityTrafficShaping.description: Indicates whether traffic shaping is supported on this interface; true(1) indicates that it is, false(2) indicates that it is not.

juniAtmIfCapabilityOam.name: juniAtmIfCapabilityOam
juniAtmIfCapabilityOam.description: Indicates whether OAM is supported on this interface; true(1) indicates that it is, false(2) indicates that it is not.

juniAtmIfCapabilityDefaultVcPerVp.name: juniAtmIfCapabilityDefaultVcPerVp
juniAtmIfCapabilityDefaultVcPerVp.description: The default number of VCs per VP for this interface.

juniAtmIfCapabilityNumVpiVciBits.name: juniAtmIfCapabilityNumVpiVciBits
juniAtmIfCapabilityNumVpiVciBits.description: The total range of bits used for constructing VPI/VCI identifiers for this interface.

juniAtmIfCapabilityMaxVcd.name: juniAtmIfCapabilityMaxVcd
juniAtmIfCapabilityMaxVcd.description: The maximum configurable value for a VCD on this interface.

juniAtmIfCapabilityMaxVpi.name: juniAtmIfCapabilityMaxVpi
juniAtmIfCapabilityMaxVpi.description: The maximum configurable value for a VPI on this interface.

juniAtmIfCapabilityMaxVci.name: juniAtmIfCapabilityMaxVci
juniAtmIfCapabilityMaxVci.description: The maximum configurable value for a VCI on this interface.

juniAtmIfCapabilityOamCellFilter.name: juniAtmIfCapabilityOamCellFilter
juniAtmIfCapabilityOamCellFilter.description: Indicates whether OAM cell filter is supported on this interface; true(1) indicates that it is, false(2) indicates that it is not.

juniAtmIfSvcSignallingTable.name: juniAtmIfSvcSignallingTable
juniAtmIfSvcSignallingTable.description: This table contains entries for extending the juniAtmIfTable for configuring signalling information for switched virtual connection (SVC).

juniAtmIfSvcSignallingEntry.name: juniAtmIfSvcSignallingEntry
juniAtmIfSvcSignallingEntry.description: Each entry provides configuration parameters for ATM signalling on the interface.

juniAtmIfSvcSignallingVpi.name: juniAtmIfSvcSignallingVpi
juniAtmIfSvcSignallingVpi.description: The VPI identifier of the ATM circuit used for signalling for this interface.

juniAtmIfSvcSignallingVci.name: juniAtmIfSvcSignallingVci
juniAtmIfSvcSignallingVci.description: The VCI identifier of the ATM circuit used for signalling for this interface.

juniAtmIfSvcSignallingVcd.name: juniAtmIfSvcSignallingVcd
juniAtmIfSvcSignallingVcd.description: An integer identifier for the ATM circuit used for signalling on this interface.

juniAtmIfSvcSignallingAdminStatus.name: juniAtmIfSvcSignallingAdminStatus
juniAtmIfSvcSignallingAdminStatus.description: The administrative status of signalling on the ATM interface.

juniAtmIfPnniRccTable.name: juniAtmIfPnniRccTable
juniAtmIfPnniRccTable.description: This table contains entries for extending the juniAtmIfTable for configuring PNNI RCC information.

juniAtmIfPnniRccEntry.name: juniAtmIfPnniRccEntry
juniAtmIfPnniRccEntry.description: Each entry provides configuration parameters for PNNI RCC on the interface.

juniAtmIfPnniRccVpi.name: juniAtmIfPnniRccVpi
juniAtmIfPnniRccVpi.description: The VPI identifier of the ATM circuit used for PNNI RCC on this interface.

juniAtmIfPnniRccVci.name: juniAtmIfPnniRccVci
juniAtmIfPnniRccVci.description: The VCI identifier of the ATM circuit used for PNNI RCC on this interface.

juniAtmIfPnniRccVcd.name: juniAtmIfPnniRccVcd
juniAtmIfPnniRccVcd.description: An integer identifier for the ATM circuit used for PNNI RCC on this interface.

juniAtmIfPnniRccAdminStatus.name: juniAtmIfPnniRccAdminStatus
juniAtmIfPnniRccAdminStatus.description: The administrative status of PNNI on the ATM interface.

juniAtmOamF4FlowEndToEndCfgTable.name: juniAtmOamF4FlowEndToEndCfgTable
juniAtmOamF4FlowEndToEndCfgTable.description: This table contains entries for F4 OAM end-to-end flows configured.

juniAtmOamF4FlowEndToEndCfgEntry.name: juniAtmOamF4FlowEndToEndCfgEntry
juniAtmOamF4FlowEndToEndCfgEntry.description: Each entry provides configuration parameters for one F4 OAM end-to-end flow configured for each VPI.

juniAtmOamF4FlowEndToEndIfIndex.name: juniAtmOamF4FlowEndToEndIfIndex
juniAtmOamF4FlowEndToEndIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the ATM interface to configure the F4 OAM end-to-end flow.

juniAtmOamF4FlowEndToEndVpi.name: juniAtmOamF4FlowEndToEndVpi
juniAtmOamF4FlowEndToEndVpi.description: Select the VPI for F4 OAM end-to-end flow configuration.

juniAtmOamF4FlowEndToEndLoopbackTimer.name: juniAtmOamF4FlowEndToEndLoopbackTimer
juniAtmOamF4FlowEndToEndLoopbackTimer.description: Configure the timer for sending the F4 flow end-to-end loopback OAM cells. Setting this value will enable sending the F4 end cells on the circuit. It is not allowed to set the value to -1 and whenever it is read as -1 that means sending end loopback is not enabled. Setting the loopback timer, other than -1, will enable sending the end cells.

juniAtmOamF4FlowEndToEndCCSink.name: juniAtmOamF4FlowEndToEndCCSink
juniAtmOamF4FlowEndToEndCCSink.description: Enable/Disable F4 flow end-to-end continuity check sink end point for this VP.

juniAtmOamF4FlowEndToEndCCSource.name: juniAtmOamF4FlowEndToEndCCSource
juniAtmOamF4FlowEndToEndCCSource.description: Enable/Disable F4 flow end-to-end continuity check source end point for this VP.

juniAtmOamF4FlowEndToEndRowStatus.name: juniAtmOamF4FlowEndToEndRowStatus
juniAtmOamF4FlowEndToEndRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy To create/delete an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: juniAtmOamF4FlowEndToEndRowStatus F4 OAM end loopback and CC tests are mutually exclusive, enabling one will disable the other automatically. So, it is not allowed either at the circuit creation time or after the circuit creation to issue a request to enable end-to-end loopback and CC tests simultaneouly. Enabling/disabling CC sink and source is one time operation. To re-enable either CC source and sink in way different to earlier, both has to be disabled from the previous.

juniAtmOamF4FlowSegmentCfgTable.name: juniAtmOamF4FlowSegmentCfgTable
juniAtmOamF4FlowSegmentCfgTable.description: This table contains entries for F4 OAM Segment flows configured.

juniAtmOamF4FlowSegmentCfgEntry.name: juniAtmOamF4FlowSegmentCfgEntry
juniAtmOamF4FlowSegmentCfgEntry.description: Each entry provides configuration parameters for one F4 OAM Segment flow configured for each VPI.

juniAtmOamF4FlowSegmentIfIndex.name: juniAtmOamF4FlowSegmentIfIndex
juniAtmOamF4FlowSegmentIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the ATM interface to configure the F4 OAM segment flow.

juniAtmOamF4FlowSegmentVpi.name: juniAtmOamF4FlowSegmentVpi
juniAtmOamF4FlowSegmentVpi.description: Select the VPI for F4 OAM segment flow configuration.

juniAtmOamF4FlowSegmentCCSink.name: juniAtmOamF4FlowSegmentCCSink
juniAtmOamF4FlowSegmentCCSink.description: Enable/Disable F4 flow segment continuity check sink end point for this VP.

juniAtmOamF4FlowSegmentCCSource.name: juniAtmOamF4FlowSegmentCCSource
juniAtmOamF4FlowSegmentCCSource.description: Enable/Disable F4 flow segment continuity check source end point for this VP.

juniAtmOamF4FlowSegmentRowStatus.name: juniAtmOamF4FlowSegmentRowStatus
juniAtmOamF4FlowSegmentRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy To create/delete an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: juniAtmOamF4FlowSegmentRowStatus Enabling/disabling CC sink and source is one time operation. To re-enable either CC source and sink in way different to earlier, both has to be disabled from the previous. F4 OAM segment loopback test is not supported.

juniAtmVpDescrTable.name: juniAtmVpDescrTable
juniAtmVpDescrTable.description: This table contains entries for ATM VP Description present in the system. The user can configure a description of up to 32 characters for every VP in the ATM interface. A row exists for every VP on the ATM interface. These rows get created as soon as the ATM major interface created.

juniAtmVpDescrEntry.name: juniAtmVpDescrEntry
juniAtmVpDescrEntry.description: Each entry contains the description of the VP.

juniAtmVpDescription.name: juniAtmVpDescription
juniAtmVpDescription.description: The description for this VP. The default value of this object is null string.

juniAtmF4FlowOamEndToEndStatsTable.name: juniAtmF4FlowOamEndToEndStatsTable
juniAtmF4FlowOamEndToEndStatsTable.description: This table contains entries for F4 flow EndToEnd OAM circuits stats.

juniAtmF4FlowOamEndToEndStatsEntry.name: juniAtmF4FlowOamEndToEndStatsEntry
juniAtmF4FlowOamEndToEndStatsEntry.description: Each entry provides stats for one F4 OAM circuit for each VPI.

juniAtmF4FlowInOamEndAisCells.name: juniAtmF4FlowInOamEndAisCells
juniAtmF4FlowInOamEndAisCells.description: Received end-to-end OAM F4 AIS cells.

juniAtmF4FlowInOamEndRdiCells.name: juniAtmF4FlowInOamEndRdiCells
juniAtmF4FlowInOamEndRdiCells.description: Received end-to-end OAM F4 RDI cells.

juniAtmF4FlowInOamEndCCCells.name: juniAtmF4FlowInOamEndCCCells
juniAtmF4FlowInOamEndCCCells.description: Received end-to-end OAM F4 CC cells.

juniAtmF4FlowInOamEndCCActDeActCells.name: juniAtmF4FlowInOamEndCCActDeActCells
juniAtmF4FlowInOamEndCCActDeActCells.description: Received end-to-end OAM F4 activation/de-activation cells.

juniAtmF4FlowInOamEndLoopbackCells.name: juniAtmF4FlowInOamEndLoopbackCells
juniAtmF4FlowInOamEndLoopbackCells.description: Total received OAM F4 end-to-end loopback cells. Aggregate of juniAtmF4FlowEndToEndInLoopbackCmds and juniAtmF4FlowEndToEndInLoopbackRsps

juniAtmF4FlowOutEndRdiCells.name: juniAtmF4FlowOutEndRdiCells
juniAtmF4FlowOutEndRdiCells.description: Transmitted end-to-end OAM F4 RDI cells.

juniAtmF4FlowOutEndCCCells.name: juniAtmF4FlowOutEndCCCells
juniAtmF4FlowOutEndCCCells.description: Transmitted end-to-end OAM F4 CC cells.

juniAtmF4FlowOutEndCCActDeActCells.name: juniAtmF4FlowOutEndCCActDeActCells

juniAtmMartiniTimeoutTimerTable.description: This table contains entries for ATM Martini cell aggregation timeout detection. The user can configure timeout values for three timers. A row exists for every separate timer supported. These rows get created as soon as the ERX system comes up.

juniAtmMartiniTimeoutTimerEntry.name: juniAtmMartiniTimeoutTimerEntry
juniAtmMartiniTimeoutTimerEntry.description: Each entry contains the timeout value of ATM Martini cell aggregation timer.

juniAtmMartiniTimeoutTimerIndex.name: juniAtmMartiniTimeoutTimerIndex
juniAtmMartiniTimeoutTimerIndex.description: The ATM Martini cell aggregation timeout timer identifier.

juniAtmMartiniTimeoutTimerValue.name: juniAtmMartiniTimeoutTimerValue
juniAtmMartiniTimeoutTimerValue.description: The ATM Martini cell aggregation timeout timer value in microseconds.

juniAtmVpStatsTable.name: juniAtmVpStatsTable
juniAtmVpStatsTable.description: This table contains entries for ATM VP statistics present in the system. A row exists for every VP on the ATM interface. These rows get created as soon as the ATM major interface created.

juniAtmVpStatsEntry.name: juniAtmVpStatsEntry
juniAtmVpStatsEntry.description: Each entry contain the VP statistics.

juniAtmVpStatsIfIndex.name: juniAtmVpStatsIfIndex
juniAtmVpStatsIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the ATM interface.

juniAtmVpStatsVpi.name: juniAtmVpStatsVpi
juniAtmVpStatsVpi.description: The VPI value of the virtual path for which statistics are retrieved.

juniAtmVpStatsInPacketErrors.name: juniAtmVpStatsInPacketErrors
juniAtmVpStatsInPacketErrors.description: Received packets dropped due to errors.

juniAtmVpStatsOutPacketErrors.name: juniAtmVpStatsOutPacketErrors
juniAtmVpStatsOutPacketErrors.description: Packets not transmitted due to errors.

juniAtmVpStatsInPacketUnknownProtocol.name: juniAtmVpStatsInPacketUnknownProtocol
juniAtmVpStatsInPacketUnknownProtocol.description: Received packets that are discarded because the interface can not discern or is not configured to support this protocol.

juniAtmVpStatsCrcErrors.name: juniAtmVpStatsCrcErrors
juniAtmVpStatsCrcErrors.description: Received packets that are discarded because of check sum erros

juniAtmVpStatsSarTimeouts.name: juniAtmVpStatsSarTimeouts
juniAtmVpStatsSarTimeouts.description: Received packets that are discarded because of SAR timeout

juniAtmVpStatsOverSizedPackets.name: juniAtmVpStatsOverSizedPackets
juniAtmVpStatsOverSizedPackets.description: Over sized packets that are received on this VP.

juniAtmAal5NextIfIndex.name: juniAtmAal5NextIfIndex
juniAtmAal5NextIfIndex.description: Coordinate ifIndex value allocation for entries in juniAtmAal5IfTable. A GET of this object returns the next available ifIndex value to be used to create an entry in the associated interface table; or zero, if no valid ifIndex value is available. This object also returns a value of zero when it is the lexicographic successor of a varbind presented in an SNMP GETNEXT or GETBULK request, for which circumstance it is assumed that ifIndex allocation is unintended. Successive GETs will typically return different values, thus avoiding collisions among cooperating management clients seeking to create table entries simultaneously.

juniAtmAal5IfTable.name: juniAtmAal5IfTable
juniAtmAal5IfTable.description: This table contains entries for ATM AAL5 interfaces present in the system.

juniAtmAal5IfEntry.name: juniAtmAal5IfEntry
juniAtmAal5IfEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of an ATM AAL5 interface. Creating/deleting entries in this table causes corresponding entries for be created/deleted in ifTable/ifXTable/juniIfTable.

juniAtmAal5IfIndex.name: juniAtmAal5IfIndex
juniAtmAal5IfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the ATM AAL5 interface. When creating entries in this table, suitable values for this object are determined by reading juniAtmAal5NextIfIndex.

juniAtmAal5IfRowStatus.name: juniAtmAal5IfRowStatus
juniAtmAal5IfRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy To create an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: juniAtmAal5IfRowStatus juniAtmAal5IfLowerIfIndex In addition, when creating an entry the following condition must hold: A value for juniAtmAal5IfIndex must have been determined previously, by reading juniAtmAal5NextIfIndex. A corresponding entry in ifTable/ifXTable/juniIfTable is created or destroyed as a result of creating/destroying an entry in this table.

juniAtmAal5IfLowerIfIndex.name: juniAtmAal5IfLowerIfIndex
juniAtmAal5IfLowerIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of an ATM interface over which this ATM AAL5 interface is to be layered. A value of zero indicates no layering. An implementation may choose to require that a nonzero value be configured at entry creation.

juniAtmBulkCircuitsNameTable.name: juniAtmBulkCircuitsNameTable
juniAtmBulkCircuitsNameTable.description: The entries in this table provide mappings of ATM bulk virtual circuit range names to local integer identifiers for those profiles. These integers are used as indexes into other MIB tables containing profile configuration parameters associated with the same profile name.

juniAtmBulkCircuitsNameEntry.name: juniAtmBulkCircuitsNameEntry
juniAtmBulkCircuitsNameEntry.description: A mapping of a ATM bulk virtual circuit range name to an integer identifier for that name.

juniAtmBulkCircuitsNameAal5IfIndex.name: juniAtmBulkCircuitsNameAal5IfIndex
juniAtmBulkCircuitsNameAal5IfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the ATM AAL5 interface.

juniAtmBulkCircuitsNameName.name: juniAtmBulkCircuitsNameName
juniAtmBulkCircuitsNameName.description: The ATM bulk virtual circuit range name uniquely identifying this entry.

juniAtmBulkCircuitsNameRowStatus.name: juniAtmBulkCircuitsNameRowStatus
juniAtmBulkCircuitsNameRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table. Only the values 'createAndGo' and 'destroy' may be SET. Creating an entry in this table creates corresponding entry in juniAtmBulkCircuitsIdTable. Deleting an entry in this table deletes corresponding entries in juniAtmBulkCircuitsIdTable, juniAtmBulkCircuitsTable and juniAtmProfileOverrideAssignIfCircuitTable.

juniAtmBulkCircuitsNameId.name: juniAtmBulkCircuitsNameId
juniAtmBulkCircuitsNameId.description: The integer identifier associated with this ATM bulk virtual circuit range name. This value of this identifier is assigned by the device when an entry in this table is created.

juniAtmBulkCircuitsIdTable.name: juniAtmBulkCircuitsIdTable
juniAtmBulkCircuitsIdTable.description: Provides inverse mapping of ATM bulk virtual circuit IDs to ATM bulk virtual circuit names.

juniAtmBulkCircuitsIdEntry.name: juniAtmBulkCircuitsIdEntry
juniAtmBulkCircuitsIdEntry.description: A mapping of an integer identifier to a ATM bulk virtual circuit name.

juniAtmBulkCircuitsIdAal5IfIndex.name: juniAtmBulkCircuitsIdAal5IfIndex
juniAtmBulkCircuitsIdAal5IfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the ATM AAL5 interface.

juniAtmBulkCircuitsIdId.name: juniAtmBulkCircuitsIdId
juniAtmBulkCircuitsIdId.description: The integer identifier associated with this ATM bulk virtual circuit name.

juniAtmBulkCircuitsIdName.name: juniAtmBulkCircuitsIdName
juniAtmBulkCircuitsIdName.description: The ATM bulk virtual circuit name having the associated identifier.

juniAtmBulkCircuitsIdNextInstance.name: juniAtmBulkCircuitsIdNextInstance
juniAtmBulkCircuitsIdNextInstance.description: The next available instance value for juniAtmBulkCircuitsEntry.

juniAtmBulkCircuitsTable.name: juniAtmBulkCircuitsTable
juniAtmBulkCircuitsTable.description: This table contains bulk virtual circuit range parameters.

juniAtmBulkCircuitsEntry.name: juniAtmBulkCircuitsEntry
juniAtmBulkCircuitsEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of VC range.

juniAtmBulkCircuitsAal5IfIndex.name: juniAtmBulkCircuitsAal5IfIndex
juniAtmBulkCircuitsAal5IfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the ATM AAL5 interface on which this bulk virtual circuit sub-range is created.

juniAtmBulkCircuitsId.name: juniAtmBulkCircuitsId
juniAtmBulkCircuitsId.description: The integer identifier associated with this ATM bulk virtual circuit name.

juniAtmBulkCircuitsInstance.name: juniAtmBulkCircuitsInstance
juniAtmBulkCircuitsInstance.description: The unique identifier of the ATM bulk virtual circuit sub-range.

juniAtmBulkCircuitsRowStatus.name: juniAtmBulkCircuitsRowStatus
juniAtmBulkCircuitsRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table. Only the values 'createAndGo' and 'destroy' may be SET. Since none of the VPI/VCI minimum and maximum values have default values, all these values must be specified before setting RowStatus to 'createAndGo'. The VPI/VCI minimum and maximum values can only be configured upon creation. Deleting an entry in this table deletes corresponding entries in juniAtmProfileOverrideAssignIfCircuitTable.

juniAtmBulkCircuitsMinVpi.name: juniAtmBulkCircuitsMinVpi
juniAtmBulkCircuitsMinVpi.description: The minimum value of VPI for this circuit sub-range. This value must be less than or equal to the value of juniAtmBulkCircuitsMaxVpi.

juniAtmBulkCircuitsMaxVpi.name: juniAtmBulkCircuitsMaxVpi
juniAtmBulkCircuitsMaxVpi.description: The maximum value of VPI for this cicuit sub-range. This value must be equal to or greater than the value of juniAtmBulkCircuitsMinVpi.

juniAtmBulkCircuitsMinVci.name: juniAtmBulkCircuitsMinVci
juniAtmBulkCircuitsMinVci.description: The minimum value of VCI for this circuit sub-range. This value must be less than or equal to the value of juniAtmBulkCircuitsMaxVci.

juniAtmBulkCircuitsMaxVci.name: juniAtmBulkCircuitsMaxVci
juniAtmBulkCircuitsMaxVci.description: The maximum value of VCI for this circuit sub-range. This value must be equal to or greater than the value of juniAtmBulkCircuitsMinVci.

juniAtmBulkCircuitsAdminState.name: juniAtmBulkCircuitsAdminState
juniAtmBulkCircuitsAdminState.description: The administrative status of this circuit sub-range.

juniAtmProfileOverrideAssignIfCircuitTab.name: juniAtmProfileOverrideAssignIfCircuitTable
juniAtmProfileOverrideAssignIfCircuitTab.description: Table providing overriding profile assignment to a circuit configured as part of bulk-configuration. Circuit is identified by interface index and vpi, vci. The entries in this table specify which profile to use when creating and configuring a dynamic interface above a circuit specified by vpi and vci. This entry is effective when the circuit specified by juniAtmProfileOverrideAssignIfCircuitAal5Index, juniAtmProfileOverrideAssignIfCircuitRangeId, juniAtmProfileOverrideAssignIfCircuitVpi, juniAtmProfileOverrideAssignIfCircuitVci is part of bulk-configuration.

juniAtmProfileOverrideAssignIfCircuitEnt.name: juniAtmProfileOverrideAssignIfCircuitEntry
juniAtmProfileOverrideAssignIfCircuitEnt.description: An assignment of a profile to a circuit configured as part of bulk-configuration on an AAL5 interface.

juniAtmProfileOverrideAssignIfCircuitAal.name: juniAtmProfileOverrideAssignIfCircuitAal5Index
juniAtmProfileOverrideAssignIfCircuitAal.description: The ifIndex of the AAL5 interface to which the profile is assigned.

juniAtmProfileOverrideAssignIfCircuitRan.name: juniAtmProfileOverrideAssignIfCircuitRangeId
juniAtmProfileOverrideAssignIfCircuitRan.description: The integer identifier associated with the ATM bulk circuit configuration.

juniAtmProfileOverrideAssignIfCircuitVpi.name: juniAtmProfileOverrideAssignIfCircuitVpi
juniAtmProfileOverrideAssignIfCircuitVpi.description: The VPI value of the circuit to which the profile is assigned.

juniAtmProfileOverrideAssignIfCircuitVci.name: juniAtmProfileOverrideAssignIfCircuitVci
juniAtmProfileOverrideAssignIfCircuitVci.description: The VCI value of the circuit to which the profile is assigned.

juniAtmProfileOverrideAssignIfCircuitRow.name: juniAtmProfileOverrideAssignIfCircuitRowStatus
juniAtmProfileOverrideAssignIfCircuitRow.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table. Only the values 'createAndGo' and 'destroy' may be SET. Since the VPI, VCI and profileId values do not have any default values, all these values must be specified before setting RowStatus to 'createAndGo'. The VPI, VCI and profileId values can only be configured upon creation. None of these values can be modified except by deleting the entry.

juniAtmProfileOverrideAssignIfCircuitPro.name: juniAtmProfileOverrideAssignIfCircuitProfileId
juniAtmProfileOverrideAssignIfCircuitPro.description: The ID of the profile assigned to the circuit configured as part of bulk-configuration. Circuit is identified by interface index and vpi, vci.

juniAtmProfileOverrideAssignIfCircuitOpe.name: juniAtmProfileOverrideAssignIfCircuitOperStatus
juniAtmProfileOverrideAssignIfCircuitOpe.description: The operational status of the profile override assignment identified by this entry. It returns inactive(0), if a static ATM circuit with identical VPI/VCI values is present on the same ATM interface. In this case, this profile override will not be used to configure upper dynamic interfaces. It returns active(1), if no static ATM circuit with identical VPI/VCI values is present on the same ATM interface. In this case, this profile override will be used to configure upper dynamic interfaces.

juniAtmSubIfNextIfIndex.name: juniAtmSubIfNextIfIndex
juniAtmSubIfNextIfIndex.description: Coordinate ifIndex value allocation for entries in juniAtmSubIfTable. A GET of this object returns the next available ifIndex value to be used to create an entry in the associated interface table; or zero, if no valid ifIndex value is available. This object also returns a value of zero when it is the lexicographic successor of a varbind presented in an SNMP GETNEXT or GETBULK request, for which circumstance it is assumed that ifIndex allocation is unintended. Successive GETs will typically return different values, thus avoiding collisions among cooperating management clients seeking to create table entries simultaneously.

juniAtmSubIfTable.name: juniAtmSubIfTable
juniAtmSubIfTable.description: This table contains entries for ATM Subinterfaces present in the system.

juniAtmSubIfEntry.name: juniAtmSubIfEntry
juniAtmSubIfEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of an ATM Subinterface. Creating/deleting entries in this table causes corresponding entries for be created/deleted in ifTable/ifXTable/juniIfTable.

juniAtmSubIfIndex.name: juniAtmSubIfIndex
juniAtmSubIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the ATM Subinterface. When creating entries in this table, suitable values for this object are determined by reading juniAtmSubNextIfIndex.

juniAtmSubIfRowStatus.name: juniAtmSubIfRowStatus
juniAtmSubIfRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy To create an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: juniAtmSubIfRowStatus juniAtmSubIfLowerIndex In addition, when creating an entry the following condition must hold: A value for juniAtmSubIfIndex must have been determined previously, by reading juniAtmSubIfNextIfIndex. A corresponding entry in ifTable/ifXTable/juniIfTable is created or destroyed as a result of creating/destroying an entry in this table.

juniAtmSubIfDistinguisher.name: juniAtmSubIfDistinguisher
juniAtmSubIfDistinguisher.description: An integer identifier for the subinterface, used in conjunction with the command-line interface. It is provided here for cross-reference purposes only. The value must be unique among subinterfaces configured on the same underlying ATM adaptation layer. The upper bound for the value is further constrained to be identical with the maximum number of subinterfaces supported by the lower interface. If this object is not configured, a value will be allocated internally and can be queried after table entry creation has succeeded.

juniAtmSubIfLowerIfIndex.name: juniAtmSubIfLowerIfIndex
juniAtmSubIfLowerIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of an ATM AAL5 interface over which this ATM subinterface is to be layered. A value of zero indicates no layering. An implementation may choose to require that a nonzero value be configured at entry creation.

juniAtmSubIfNbma.name: juniAtmSubIfNbma
juniAtmSubIfNbma.description: The NBMA administrative setting. Setting this value of this object to true(1) will enable multipoint access on this interface. Setting the value to false(2), will enable point to point access on this interface.

juniAtmSubIfAddress.name: juniAtmSubIfAddress
juniAtmSubIfAddress.description: Specifies the local ATM NSAP address of the circuit. A GET operation returns a full 20-octet NSAP. A SET operation only requires 7 octets, since the prefix can be implied.

juniAtmSubIfMtu.name: juniAtmSubIfMtu
juniAtmSubIfMtu.description: The size of the largest packet which can be sent/received on the interface, specified in octets.

juniAtmSubIfAdvisoryRxSpeed.name: juniAtmSubIfAdvisoryRxSpeed
juniAtmSubIfAdvisoryRxSpeed.description: Advisory receive speed, in kilobits per second (kbps), of this subinterface. This object has no impact on forwarding performance but may be used as a hint for underlying circuit receive speed.

juniAtmSubIfMartiniMaxCellsPerPacket.name: juniAtmSubIfMartiniMaxCellsPerPacket
juniAtmSubIfMartiniMaxCellsPerPacket.description: The number of cells that can be aggregated in a single ATM Martini packet in cell-relay mode.

juniAtmSubIfMartiniTimeoutTimerId.name: juniAtmSubIfMartiniTimeoutTimerId
juniAtmSubIfMartiniTimeoutTimerId.description: The timer identifier used to abandon cell aggregation when no cells are supplied for transmission in ATM Martini cell-relay mode.

juniAtmSubIfAssociatedVcClassId.name: juniAtmSubIfAssociatedVcClassId
juniAtmSubIfAssociatedVcClassId.description: The integer identifier of the ATM VC class associated with this ATM sub interface. A value for this identifier is determined by locating or creating an ATM VC class name in the juniAtmVcClassNameTable. A value of 0 means no VC class association exists for this interface.

juniAtmSubIfVccTable.name: juniAtmSubIfVccTable
juniAtmSubIfVccTable.description: This table contains entries for ATM VCCs configured on ATM subinterfaces present in the system. An implementation may constrain the number of VCCs permitted to be configured per ATM Subinterface; in particular, an implementation may restrict each ATM Subinterface to have a single VCC. Attributes in this entry can only be configured at entry creation, and remain fixed for the lifetime of the entry.

juniAtmSubIfVccEntry.name: juniAtmSubIfVccEntry
juniAtmSubIfVccEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of an ATM subinterface VCC.

juniAtmSubIfVccVpi.name: juniAtmSubIfVccVpi
juniAtmSubIfVccVpi.description: The VPI of the ATM VCC used by this subinterface.

juniAtmSubIfVccVci.name: juniAtmSubIfVccVci
juniAtmSubIfVccVci.description: The VCI of the ATM VCC used by this subinterface.

juniAtmSubIfVccRowStatus.name: juniAtmSubIfVccRowStatus
juniAtmSubIfVccRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy To create an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: juniAtmSubIfVccRowStatus In addition, when creating an entry the following conditions must hold: The ATM Subinterface identified by juniAtmSubIfIndex must exist. A positive value configured for juniAtmSubIfVccVcd must not already be assigned to an existing VCC. For each value of juniAtmSubIfVccServiceCategory, additional dependent objects in the entry require configuration as identified here: juniAtmSubIfVccServiceCategory Requires configuration of: ------------------------------------------------------------ ubr <none> ubrPcr juniAtmSubIfVccPcr nrtVbr juniAtmSubIfVccPcr juniAtmSubIfVccScr juniAtmSubIfVccMbs cbr juniAtmSubIfVccPcr rtVbr juniAtmSubIfVccPcr juniAtmSubIfVccScr juniAtmSubIfVccMbs ------------------------------------------------------------ Attributes in this entry can only be configured at entry creation, and remain fixed for the lifetime of the entry.

juniAtmSubIfVccVcd.name: juniAtmSubIfVccVcd
juniAtmSubIfVccVcd.description: An integer identifier for the circuit, used in conjunction with the command-line interface. It is provided here for cross-reference purposes only. The value must be unique among VCCs configured on the same underlying ATM interface. If this object is not configured, or is configured with a value of zero, a value will be allocated internally and can be queried after table entry creation has succeeded.

juniAtmSubIfVccType.name: juniAtmSubIfVccType
juniAtmSubIfVccType.description: Specifies the encapsulation used by the circuit to carry IP datagrams. Encapsulations are as specified in RFC1483 Multiprotocol Interconnect over ATM. The 'autoconfig' value will recognize both VcMux and LLC formats. The 'aal5' and 'aal0' values are used for encapsulation methods for transport of ATM frames and cells over IP and MPLS networks when no encapsulation method is specified.

juniAtmSubIfVccServiceCategory.name: juniAtmSubIfVccServiceCategory
juniAtmSubIfVccServiceCategory.description: Service category for this circuit: ubr Unspecified Bit Rate (best effort). ubrPcr Unspecified Bit Rate with Peak Cell Rate limit. nrtVbr Non-RealTime Variable Bit Rate. cbr Constant Bit Rate. rtVbr Realtime Variable Bit Rate.

juniAtmSubIfVccPcr.name: juniAtmSubIfVccPcr
juniAtmSubIfVccPcr.description: Peak Cell Rate, in kilobits per second (kbps), of this circuit. This parameter is only required when juniAtmSubIfVccServiceCategory is configured to have one of the following values: ubrPcr nrtVbr cbr rtVbr

juniAtmSubIfVccScr.name: juniAtmSubIfVccScr
juniAtmSubIfVccScr.description: Sustained Cell Rate, in kilobits per second (kbps), of this circuit. This parameter is only required when juniAtmSubIfVccServiceCategory is configured to have the following value: nrtVbr rtVbr

juniAtmSubIfVccMbs.name: juniAtmSubIfVccMbs
juniAtmSubIfVccMbs.description: Maximum Burst Size, in cells, of this circuit. This parameter is only required when juniAtmSubIfVccServiceCategory is configured to have the following value: nrtVbr rtVbr

juniAtmSubIfInverseArp.name: juniAtmSubIfInverseArp
juniAtmSubIfInverseArp.description: Enables the inverse ARP protocol on this VCC; true(1) enables the protocol, false(2) disables it.

juniAtmSubIfInverseArpRefresh.name: juniAtmSubIfInverseArpRefresh
juniAtmSubIfInverseArpRefresh.description: The refresh rate in minutes between inverse ARP protocol messages.

juniAtmSubIfVccAssociatedVcClassId.name: juniAtmSubIfVccAssociatedVcClassId
juniAtmSubIfVccAssociatedVcClassId.description: The integer identifier of the ATM VC class associated with this ATM sub interface. A value for this identifier is determined by locating or creating an ATM VC class name in the juniAtmVcClassNameTable. A value of 0 means no VC class association exists for this VC.

juniAtmCircuitOamTable.name: juniAtmCircuitOamTable
juniAtmCircuitOamTable.description: This table contains circuit OAM data for a PVC.

juniAtmCircuitOamEntry.name: juniAtmCircuitOamEntry
juniAtmCircuitOamEntry.description: Each entry provides OAM data on an ATM PVC.

juniAtmCircuitOamIfIndex.name: juniAtmCircuitOamIfIndex
juniAtmCircuitOamIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the ATM subinterface.

juniAtmCircuitOamVpi.name: juniAtmCircuitOamVpi
juniAtmCircuitOamVpi.description: The VPI of the ATM VCC used by this ATM interface and PVC.

juniAtmCircuitOamVci.name: juniAtmCircuitOamVci
juniAtmCircuitOamVci.description: The VCI of the ATM VCC used by this ATM interface and PVC.

juniAtmCircuitOamAdminStatus.name: juniAtmCircuitOamAdminStatus
juniAtmCircuitOamAdminStatus.description: The administrative state of OAM for the interface identified by this entry.

juniAtmCircuitOamLoopbackOperStatus.name: juniAtmCircuitOamLoopbackOperStatus
juniAtmCircuitOamLoopbackOperStatus.description: The operational status of OAM for the interface identified by this entry. oamOperStatusNotSupported(0) - OAM not supported on this interface oamOperStatusDisabled(1) - VC integrity disabled oamOperStatusSent(2) - Loopback sent, awaiting response oamOperStatusReceived(3) - Loopback response received, awaiting frequency oamOperStatusFailed(4) - Loopback response not received, or invalid response received

juniAtmCircuitVcOamOperStatus.name: juniAtmCircuitVcOamOperStatus
juniAtmCircuitVcOamOperStatus.description: The OAM VC operational status of this entry. oamVcOperStateAisState(0) - AIS cell received or underlying physical layer reporting transmission path AIS oamVcOperStateRdiState(1) - RDI cell received oamVcOperStateDownRetry(2) - OAM loopback failed, using retry frequency to verify that the VC is really down oamVcOperStateUpRetry(3) - OAM loopback successful, using retry frequency to verify that the VC is really up oamVcOperStateUp(4) - OAM loopback successful after up retry verification oamVcOperStateDown(5) - OAM loopback failed after down retry verification oamVcOperStateNotManaged(6)- No verification via loopback cells being performed oamVcOperStateVpAis(7) - F4 AIS cell received oamVcOperStateVpRdi(8) - F4 RDI cell received oamVcOperStateVcInVpRdi(9) - F4 RDI cell received; path failure oamVcOperStateVcInVpAis(10)- F4 AIS cell received; path failure oamVcOperStateSegAis(11) - Segment AIS cell received oamVcOperStateSegRdi(12) - Segment RDI cell received oamVcOperStateGenAis(13) - Connection failure; generating AIS cells.

juniAtmCircuitOamLoopbackFrequency.name: juniAtmCircuitOamLoopbackFrequency
juniAtmCircuitOamLoopbackFrequency.description: The OAM loopback frequency in seconds.

juniAtmCircuitInOamCellsDropped.name: juniAtmCircuitInOamCellsDropped
juniAtmCircuitInOamCellsDropped.description: Received OAM cells that were dropped.

juniAtmCircuitInOamF5EndToEndLoopbackCel.name: juniAtmCircuitInOamF5EndToEndLoopbackCells
juniAtmCircuitInOamF5EndToEndLoopbackCel.description: Total received OAM F5 end-to-end loopback cells. Aggregate of juniAtmCircuitInOamF5EndToEndLoopbackCmds and juniAtmCircuitInOamF5EndToEndLoopbackRsps

juniAtmCircuitInOamF5SegmentLoopbackCell.name: juniAtmCircuitInOamF5SegmentLoopbackCells
juniAtmCircuitInOamF5SegmentLoopbackCell.description: Total received OAM F5 segment loopback cells. Aggregate of juniAtmCircuitInOamF5SegmentLoopbackCmds and juniAtmCircuitInOamF5SegmentLoopbackRsps

juniAtmCircuitOutOamF5EndToEndLoopbackCe.name: juniAtmCircuitOutOamF5EndToEndLoopbackCells
juniAtmCircuitOutOamF5EndToEndLoopbackCe.description: Total transmitted OAM F5 end-to-end loopback cells. Aggregate of juniAtmCircuitOutOamF5EndToEndLoopbackCmds and juniAtmCircuitOutOamF5EndToEndLoopbackRsps

juniAtmCircuitOutOamF5SegmentLoopbackCel.name: juniAtmCircuitOutOamF5SegmentLoopbackCells
juniAtmCircuitOutOamF5SegmentLoopbackCel.description: Total transmitted OAM F5 segment loopback cells. Aggregate of juniAtmCircuitOutOamF5SegmentLoopbackCmds and juniAtmCircuitOutOamF5SegmentLoopbackRsps

juniAtmCircuitInOamF5EndToEndLoopbackCmd.name: juniAtmCircuitInOamF5EndToEndLoopbackCmds
juniAtmCircuitInOamF5EndToEndLoopbackCmd.description: Received OAM F5 end-to-end loopback commands.

juniAtmCircuitInOamF5EndToEndLoopbackRsp.name: juniAtmCircuitInOamF5EndToEndLoopbackRsps
juniAtmCircuitInOamF5EndToEndLoopbackRsp.description: Received OAM F5 end-to-end loopback responses.

juniAtmCircuitInOamF5SegmentLoopbackCmds.name: juniAtmCircuitInOamF5SegmentLoopbackCmds
juniAtmCircuitInOamF5SegmentLoopbackCmds.description: Received OAM F5 segment loopback commands.

juniAtmCircuitInOamF5SegmentLoopbackRsps.name: juniAtmCircuitInOamF5SegmentLoopbackRsps
juniAtmCircuitInOamF5SegmentLoopbackRsps.description: Received OAM F5 segment loopback responses.

juniAtmCircuitOutOamF5EndToEndLoopbackCm.name: juniAtmCircuitOutOamF5EndToEndLoopbackCmds
juniAtmCircuitOutOamF5EndToEndLoopbackCm.description: Transmitted OAM F5 end-to-end loopback commands.

juniAtmCircuitOutOamF5EndToEndLoopbackRs.name: juniAtmCircuitOutOamF5EndToEndLoopbackRsps
juniAtmCircuitOutOamF5EndToEndLoopbackRs.description: Transmitted OAM F5 end-to-end loopback responses.

juniAtmCircuitOutOamF5SegmentLoopbackCmd.name: juniAtmCircuitOutOamF5SegmentLoopbackCmds
juniAtmCircuitOutOamF5SegmentLoopbackCmd.description: Transmitted OAM F5 segment loopback commands.

juniAtmCircuitOutOamF5SegmentLoopbackRsp.name: juniAtmCircuitOutOamF5SegmentLoopbackRsps
juniAtmCircuitOutOamF5SegmentLoopbackRsp.description: Transmitted OAM F5 segment loopback responses.

juniAtmCircuitOamUpCount.name: juniAtmCircuitOamUpCount
juniAtmCircuitOamUpCount.description: Specifies the number of successive loopback cell responses to receive before a PVC is up for connectivity verification.

juniAtmCircuitOamDownCount.name: juniAtmCircuitOamDownCount
juniAtmCircuitOamDownCount.description: Specifies the number of successive loopback cell responses not received before declaring a PVC down for connectivity verification.

juniAtmCircuitOamRetryFrequency.name: juniAtmCircuitOamRetryFrequency
juniAtmCircuitOamRetryFrequency.description: Specifies the frequency (in seconds) to transmit loopback cells when verifying PVC state (up or down) for connectivity verification.

juniAtmCircuitOamAlarmDownCount.name: juniAtmCircuitOamAlarmDownCount
juniAtmCircuitOamAlarmDownCount.description: Specifies the number of successive alarm (AIS or RDI) cells to receive before declaring a PVC down.

juniAtmCircuitOamAlarmClearTimeout.name: juniAtmCircuitOamAlarmClearTimeout
juniAtmCircuitOamAlarmClearTimeout.description: Specifies how long to wait (in seconds) before declaring a PVC up after it has stopped receiving alarm cells.

juniAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingTable.name: juniAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingTable
juniAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingTable.description: This table contains entries for traffic shaping of ATM VCCs configured on ATM subinterfaces present in the system. This table augments the juniAtmSubIfVccTable only for VCCs that support traffic shapping. Attributes in this entry can only be configured at entry creation, and remain fixed for the lifetime of the entry.

juniAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingEntry.name: juniAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingEntry
juniAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingEntry.description: Each entry describes the traffic shping characteristics of an ATM subinterface VCC.

juniAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingCdvt.name: juniAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingCdvt
juniAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingCdvt.description: The network cell delay variation tolerance (CDVT) in tenths of a microsecond.

juniAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingClp0.name: juniAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingClp0
juniAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingClp0.description: Specifies whether or not only CLP0 cells are to be policed according to the traffic contract. CLP1 cells are forwarded on a best-effort basis CLP-significant model for (VBR.2, VBR.3 conformance). Applicable only for VBR circuits.

juniAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingTagging.name: juniAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingTagging
juniAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingTagging.description: Specifies whether or not CLP0 cells should be tagged for SCR policing (VBR.3 conformance). Applicable only for VBR circuits.

juniAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingPoliceObser.name: juniAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingPoliceObserve
juniAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingPoliceObser.description: Specifies whether of not no policing action is to be taken (note the double negative; if true(1) then no policing action will be taken; if false(2) then policing action will be taken). Regardless of the state of this object, all counters will be incremented.

juniAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingPacketShapi.name: juniAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingPacketShaping
juniAtmSubIfVccTrafficShapingPacketShapi.description: Specifies whether of not to shape output traffic on a packet boundary.

juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigTable.name: juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigTable
juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigTable.description: This table contains entries for extending the juniAtmSubIfTable to configure switched virtual connection (SVC) on the subinterfaces.

juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigEntry.name: juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigEntry
juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigEntry.description: Each entry provides configuration parameters for an ATM SVC on the subinterface.

juniAtmSubIfSvcRowStatus.name: juniAtmSubIfSvcRowStatus
juniAtmSubIfSvcRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy

juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigDestAtmAddress.name: juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigDestAtmAddress
juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigDestAtmAddress.description: Specifies the destination ATM NSAP address of the circuit.

juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigCircuitType.name: juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigCircuitType
juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigCircuitType.description: Specifies the encapsulation used by the circuit to carry IP datagrams. Encapsulations are as specified in RFC1483 Multiprotocol Interconnect over ATM.

juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigServiceCategory.name: juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigServiceCategory
juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigServiceCategory.description: Service category for this circuit: ubr Unspecified Bit Rate (best effort). ubrPcr Unspecified Bit Rate with Peak Cell Rate limit. nrtVbr Non-RealTime Variable Bit Rate. cbr Constant Bit Rate. rtVbr Realtime Variable Bit Rate.

juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigPcr.name: juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigPcr
juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigPcr.description: Peak Cell Rate, in kilo-bits per second (kbps), of this circuit.

juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigScr.name: juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigScr
juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigScr.description: Sustained Cell Rate, in kilo-bits per second (kbps), of this circuit.

juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigMbs.name: juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigMbs
juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigMbs.description: Maximum Burst Size, in cells, of this circuit.

juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigCdvt.name: juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigCdvt
juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigCdvt.description: Specify the network Cell Delay Variation Tolerance.

juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigClp0.name: juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigClp0
juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigClp0.description: Specify that only CLP0 cells are to be policed according to the traffic contract. CLP1 cells are forwarded on a best-effort basis CLP-significant model for (VBR.2, VBR.3 conformance).

juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigTagging.name: juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigTagging
juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigTagging.description: Specify that CLP0 cells should be tagged for SCR policing (VBR.3 conformance).

juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigObserve.name: juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigObserve
juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigObserve.description: Specify that no policing action is to be taken; only counters are incremented.

juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigPacketDiscard.name: juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigPacketDiscard
juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigPacketDiscard.description: Enable early packet Discard for this circuit.

juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigDestE164Address.name: juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigDestE164Address
juniAtmSubIfSvcConfigDestE164Address.description: Specifies the destination ATM E164 address of the circuit.

juniAtmSubIfDescriptionExport.name: juniAtmSubIfDescriptionExport
juniAtmSubIfDescriptionExport.description: Enabling of this object will program the subinterface description down to the applicable line card. Note, the subinterface description sent down to the line card is a truncated version (32 bytes) of the ifAlias.

juniAtmNbmaMapTable.name: juniAtmNbmaMapTable
juniAtmNbmaMapTable.description: This table contains entries for ATM NBMA maps.

juniAtmNbmaMapEntry.name: juniAtmNbmaMapEntry
juniAtmNbmaMapEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of an ATM NBMA map.

juniAtmNbmaMapVcd.name: juniAtmNbmaMapVcd
juniAtmNbmaMapVcd.description: An integer identifier for the ATM circuit, used in conjunction with the command-line interface. The value must be unique among VCs configured on the same ATM interface.

juniAtmNbmaMapIpAddress.name: juniAtmNbmaMapIpAddress
juniAtmNbmaMapIpAddress.description: The IP address associated with this entry.

juniAtmNbmaMapVpi.name: juniAtmNbmaMapVpi
juniAtmNbmaMapVpi.description: The VPI identifier of the ATM circuit.

juniAtmNbmaMapVci.name: juniAtmNbmaMapVci
juniAtmNbmaMapVci.description: The VCI identifier of the ATM circuit.

juniAtmNbmaMapIfIndex.name: juniAtmNbmaMapIfIndex
juniAtmNbmaMapIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the ATM major interface associated with this entry. The value of this object will be zero when the map is not applied to an interface.

juniAtmNbmaMapBroadcast.name: juniAtmNbmaMapBroadcast
juniAtmNbmaMapBroadcast.description: The broadcast enable/disable setting for this entry. The value true(1) enable broadcast support; disable(2) disabled broadcast support for this entry.

juniAtmNbmaMapRowStatus.name: juniAtmNbmaMapRowStatus
juniAtmNbmaMapRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy Additional notes to aid the network manager: - NBMA maps are not supported on dynamic interface. - NBMA maps can only be applied to a single major ATM interface at a time. - NBMA maps cannot be deleted unless the map is removed from the ATM interface (juniAtmNbmaMapIfIndex = 0). - The values of juniAtmNbmaMapVpi, juniAtmNbmaMapVci and juniAtmNbmaMapIfIndex are zero until the map is applied to a major ATM interface. - To create an entry in this table, the following objects must be present in the set PDU: juniAtmNbmaMapIpAddress juniAtmNbmaMapBroadcast juniAtmNbmaMapRowStatus - Once created, only the following objects can be modified: juniAtmNbmaMapBroadcast

juniAtmNbmaMapListTable.name: juniAtmNbmaMapListTable
juniAtmNbmaMapListTable.description: This table contains entries for ATM NBMA map lists.

juniAtmNbmaMapListEntry.name: juniAtmNbmaMapListEntry
juniAtmNbmaMapListEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of an ATM NBMA map.

juniAtmNbmaMapListRowStatus.name: juniAtmNbmaMapListRowStatus
juniAtmNbmaMapListRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy

juniAtmPingTestOamSeg.name: juniAtmPingTestOamSeg
juniAtmPingTestOamSeg.description: This identifies an OAM Ping (multiple loopbacks) Test on a VPL, VPC, VCL, or VCC termination point, using segment OAM cells. The test type must have appended to it a code that uniquely identifies an intermediate point responsible for looping back each cell. If this is absent, the loopbacks are performed at the end of the segment or connection. E.g., the OID { juniAtmPingTestOamSeg 5 } identifies that the loopbacks should be performed at the intermediate point labeled 5.

juniAtmPingTestOamE2E.name: juniAtmPingTestOamE2E
juniAtmPingTestOamE2E.description: This identifies an OAM Ping (multiple loopbacks) Test on a VPL, VPC, VCL, or VCC termination point, using end-to-end OAM cells.

juniAtmVpPingTable.name: juniAtmVpPingTable
juniAtmVpPingTable.description: This table contains entries for extending the ATM-FORUM-SNMP-M4-MIB atmM4VpTestTable to do ping (multiple loopback) type testing.

juniAtmVpPingEntry.name: juniAtmVpPingEntry
juniAtmVpPingEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics, status and results of the most recent ATM ping test.

juniAtmVpPingProbeCount.name: juniAtmVpPingProbeCount
juniAtmVpPingProbeCount.description: The number of ping probes (OAM cells) to be sent to complete the test.

juniAtmVpPingTimeOut.name: juniAtmVpPingTimeOut
juniAtmVpPingTimeOut.description: Specifies the time-out value, in seconds, for a remote ping operation.

juniAtmVpPingCtlTrapGeneration.name: juniAtmVpPingCtlTrapGeneration
juniAtmVpPingCtlTrapGeneration.description: The value of this object determines when and if to generate a notification for this entry: testCompletion(0) - Generate a juniPingTestCompleted notification. The value of this object defaults to zero, indicating that no notification has been selected.

juniAtmVpPingSentProbes.name: juniAtmVpPingSentProbes
juniAtmVpPingSentProbes.description: The number of ping probes (OAM cells) that have been sent thus far for this test. The value of this object MUST be set to zero when the atmfM4VpTestStatus object transitions from notInUse(0) to inUse(1).

juniAtmVpPingProbeResponses.name: juniAtmVpPingProbeResponses
juniAtmVpPingProbeResponses.description: The number of ping responses that have been received thus far for this test. The value of this object MUST be set to zero when the atmfM4VpTestStatus object transitions from notInUse(0) to inUse(1).

juniAtmVpPingStartTime.name: juniAtmVpPingStartTime
juniAtmVpPingStartTime.description: The time (sysUpTime) when the test started.

juniAtmVpPingMinRtt.name: juniAtmVpPingMinRtt
juniAtmVpPingMinRtt.description: The shortest round-trip-time (RTT) for the pings that have received responses. The value of this object MUST be set to zero when the atmfM4VpTestStatus object transitions from notInUse(0) to inUse(1). A value of zero for this object implies that no ping responses have been received for the current test.

juniAtmVpPingMaxRtt.name: juniAtmVpPingMaxRtt
juniAtmVpPingMaxRtt.description: The longest round-trip-time (RTT) for the pings that have received responses. The value of this object MUST be set to zero when the atmfM4VpTestStatus object transitions from notInUse(0) to inUse(1). A value of zero for this object implies that no ping responses have been received for the current test.

juniAtmVpPingAverageRtt.name: juniAtmVpPingAverageRtt
juniAtmVpPingAverageRtt.description: The average round-trip-time (RTT) for all the pings that have received responses. The value of this object MUST be set to zero when the atmfM4VpTestStatus object transitions from notInUse(0) to inUse(1). A value of zero for this object implies that no ping responses have been received for the current test.

juniAtmVcPingTable.name: juniAtmVcPingTable
juniAtmVcPingTable.description: This table contains entries for extending the ATM-FORUM-SNMP-M4-MIB atmM4VcTestTable to do ping (multiple loopback) type testing.

juniAtmVcPingEntry.name: juniAtmVcPingEntry
juniAtmVcPingEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics, status and results of the most recent ATM ping test.

juniAtmVcPingProbeCount.name: juniAtmVcPingProbeCount
juniAtmVcPingProbeCount.description: The number of ping probes (OAM cells) to be sent to complete the test.

juniAtmVcPingTimeOut.name: juniAtmVcPingTimeOut
juniAtmVcPingTimeOut.description: Specifies the time-out value, in seconds, for a remote ping operation.

juniAtmVcPingCtlTrapGeneration.name: juniAtmVcPingCtlTrapGeneration
juniAtmVcPingCtlTrapGeneration.description: The value of this object determines when and if to generate a notification for this entry: testCompletion(0) - Generate a juniPingTestCompleted notification. The value of this object defaults to zero, indicating that no notification has been selected.

juniAtmVcPingSentProbes.name: juniAtmVcPingSentProbes
juniAtmVcPingSentProbes.description: The number of ping probes (OAM cells) that have been sent thus far for this test. The value of this object MUST be set to zero when the atmfM4VcTestStatus object transitions from notInUse(0) to inUse(1).

juniAtmVcPingProbeResponses.name: juniAtmVcPingProbeResponses
juniAtmVcPingProbeResponses.description: The number of ping responses that have been received thus far for this test. The value of this object MUST be set to zero when the atmfM4VcTestStatus object transitions from notInUse(0) to inUse(1).

juniAtmVcPingStartTime.name: juniAtmVcPingStartTime
juniAtmVcPingStartTime.description: The time (sysUpTime) when the test started.

juniAtmVcPingMinRtt.name: juniAtmVcPingMinRtt
juniAtmVcPingMinRtt.description: The shortest round-trip-time (RTT) for the pings that have received responses. The value of this object MUST be set to zero when the atmfM4VcTestStatus object transitions from notInUse(0) to inUse(1). A value of zero for this object implies that no ping responses have been received for the current test.

juniAtmVcPingMaxRtt.name: juniAtmVcPingMaxRtt
juniAtmVcPingMaxRtt.description: The longest round-trip-time (RTT) for the pings that have received responses. The value of this object MUST be set to zero when the atmfM4VcTestStatus object transitions from notInUse(0) to inUse(1). A value of zero for this object implies that no ping responses have been received for the current test.

juniAtmVcPingAverageRtt.name: juniAtmVcPingAverageRtt
juniAtmVcPingAverageRtt.description: The average round-trip-time (RTT) for all the pings that have received responses. The value of this object MUST be set to zero when the atmfM4VcTestStatus object transitions from notInUse(0) to inUse(1). A value of zero for this object implies that no ping responses have been received for the current test.

juniAtmPingTestCodeOamDisabled.name: juniAtmPingTestCodeOamDisabled
juniAtmPingTestCodeOamDisabled.description: This test code indicates that the ATM ping operation cannot be initiated or is aborted because the juniAtmIfOamCellRxAdminState is set to disabled.

juniAtmPingTestCodeCircuitDown.name: juniAtmPingTestCodeCircuitDown
juniAtmPingTestCodeCircuitDown.description: This test code indicates that the ATM ping operation cannot be initiated or is aborted because the operational status of the ATM circuit is down.

juniAtmPingTestCodeStopped.name: juniAtmPingTestCodeStopped
juniAtmPingTestCodeStopped.description: This test code indicates that the ATM ping operation is administratively stopped by an External Management.

juniAtmPingTestCodeOamVcOperState.name: juniAtmPingTestCodeOamVcOperState
juniAtmPingTestCodeOamVcOperState.description: This test code indicates that the ATM ping operation cannot be initiated or is aborted because the circuit is down because of a OAM fault condition. This is possible if juniAtmCircuitVcOamOperStatus is one of the following: oamVcOperStateAisState(0) - AIS cell received or underlying physical layer reporting transmission path AIS. oamVcOperStateRdiState(1) - RDI cell received.

juniAtmPingTestCodeMaxPingCountReached.name: juniAtmPingTestCodeMaxPingCountReached
juniAtmPingTestCodeMaxPingCountReached.description: This test code indicates that the ping operation cannot be initiated as the maximum number of ping possible on this interfaces exceeds the allowable limit.

juniAtmPingTestCodeInvalidParams.name: juniAtmPingTestCodeInvalidParams
juniAtmPingTestCodeInvalidParams.description: This Test Code identities the Ping operation cannot be initiated as one or more of the Ping Parameters is Invalid.

juniAtmVcClassNameTable.name: juniAtmVcClassNameTable
juniAtmVcClassNameTable.description: The entries in this table provide mappings of ATM VC class names to local integer identifiers. These integers are used as indexes into other MIB tables containing ATM VC attributes associated with the same VC class name.

juniAtmVcClassNameEntry.name: juniAtmVcClassNameEntry

juniAtmVcClassName.name: juniAtmVcClassName
juniAtmVcClassName.description: The ATM VC class name uniquely identifying this entry.

juniAtmVcClassNameRowStatus.name: juniAtmVcClassNameRowStatus
juniAtmVcClassNameRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table. Only the values 'createAndGo' ,'destroy', 'active' and 'notInService' may be SET. The SNMP manager would set the row status to notInService before making any VC class attribute changes explained in juniAtmVcClassTable. Once the VC class attribute changes are complete, the SNMP manager would set the row status to active, upon which the VC class attribute changes would be committed. Any ATM VC class attribute changes that are made when the row status is 'active' are committed right away.

juniAtmVcClassNameId.name: juniAtmVcClassNameId
juniAtmVcClassNameId.description: The integer identifier associated with this VC class name. The value of this identifier is assigned by the device when an entry in this table is created.

juniAtmVcClassIdTable.name: juniAtmVcClassIdTable
juniAtmVcClassIdTable.description: Provides inverse mapping of ATM VC class IDs to ATM VC class names.

juniAtmVcClassIdEntry.name: juniAtmVcClassIdEntry
juniAtmVcClassIdEntry.description: A mapping of an integer identifier to an ATM VC class name.

juniAtmVcClassIdId.name: juniAtmVcClassIdId
juniAtmVcClassIdId.description: The integer identifier associated with this ATM VC class name.

juniAtmVcClassIdName.name: juniAtmVcClassIdName
juniAtmVcClassIdName.description: The ATM VC class name having the associated identifier.

juniAtmVcClassTable.name: juniAtmVcClassTable
juniAtmVcClassTable.description: This table contains Juniper ATM VC Class entries which can be used to specify the ATM PVC attributes either at creation or modification time. A row in this table with default values is created when an entry in juniAtmVcClassNameTable is created.

juniAtmVcClassEntry.name: juniAtmVcClassEntry
juniAtmVcClassEntry.description: Each entry contains the attributes of the ATM VC which would be applied to the VC either at creation or modification time when this ATM VC class is associated to it.

juniAtmVcClassId.name: juniAtmVcClassId
juniAtmVcClassId.description: The integer identifier associated with this ATM VC class. A value for this identifier is determined by locating or creating an ATM VC class name in the juniAtmVcClassNameTable.

juniAtmVcClassVccType.name: juniAtmVcClassVccType
juniAtmVcClassVccType.description: Specifies the encapsulation used by the circuit to carry IP datagrams. Encapsulations are as specified in RFC1483 Multiprotocol Interconnect over ATM. The 'autoconfig' value will recognize both VC Mux and LLC formats. The 'aal5' and 'aal0' values are used for encapsulation methods for transport of ATM frames and cells over IP and MPLS networks when no encapsulation method is specified.

juniAtmVcClassVccServiceCategory.name: juniAtmVcClassVccServiceCategory
juniAtmVcClassVccServiceCategory.description: Service category for this circuit: ubr Unspecified Bit Rate (best effort). ubrPcr Unspecified Bit Rate with Peak Cell Rate limit. nrtVbr Non-RealTime Variable Bit Rate. cbr Constant Bit Rate. rtVbr Realtime Variable Bit Rate.

juniAtmVcClassVccScr.name: juniAtmVcClassVccScr
juniAtmVcClassVccScr.description: Sustained Cell Rate, in kilobits per second (kbps), of this circuit. This parameter is only required when juniAtmVcClassVccServiceCategory is configured to have the following value: nrtVbr rtVbr

juniAtmVcClassVccMbs.name: juniAtmVcClassVccMbs
juniAtmVcClassVccMbs.description: Maximum Burst Size, in cells, of this circuit. This parameter is only required when juniAtmVcClassVccServiceCategory is configured to have the following value: nrtVbr rtVbr

juniAtmVcClassVccOamAdminStatus.name: juniAtmVcClassVccOamAdminStatus
juniAtmVcClassVccOamAdminStatus.description: The OAM VC integrity administrative state of the ATM VC associated with this class.

juniAtmVcClassVccOamLoopbackFrequency.name: juniAtmVcClassVccOamLoopbackFrequency

juniAtmVcClassVccOamDownCount.name: juniAtmVcClassVccOamDownCount

juniAtmVcClassVccOamRetryFrequency.name: juniAtmVcClassVccOamRetryFrequency
juniAtmVcClassVccOamRetryFrequency.description: Specifies the frequency (in seconds) to transmit loopback cells when verifying the ATM VC operational state associated with this class (up or down) for connectivity verification.

juniAtmVcClassVccOamAlarmDownCount.name: juniAtmVcClassVccOamAlarmDownCount
juniAtmVcClassVccOamAlarmDownCount.description: Specifies the number of successive alarm (AIS or RDI) cells to receive before declaring the ATM VC associated with class as down.

juniAtmVcClassVccOamAlarmClearTimeout.name: juniAtmVcClassVccOamAlarmClearTimeout
juniAtmVcClassVccOamAlarmClearTimeout.description: Specifies how long to wait (in seconds) before declaring the ATM VC associated with class as up after it has stopped receiving alarm cells.

juniAtmVcClassVccInverseArp.name: juniAtmVcClassVccInverseArp
juniAtmVcClassVccInverseArp.description: Enables the inverse ARP protocol on the ATM VC associated with this class; true(1) enables the protocol, false(2) disables it.
